        <body>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>St. Thomas</placeName>
                <date>10<hi rend="sup">th</hi> Feb. 1862</date>.</p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Dear Sir.</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">I have been requested to forward you<lb/> the bridal cards which I
                have the pleasure of enclosing here„<lb/>with. The nuptials of my sister were
                celebrated last week.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">There has lately appeared in our paper an un„<lb/>warranted and
                unbecoming attack on <persName>Mr. Myers</persName> on account<lb/> of his friends'
                using the title of “Rev. Dr.” before his name. The<lb/> Representatives of our
                congregation immediately deemed it their<lb/> duty to speak in <persName>Mr.
                    Myers'</persName> vindication. According to an article<lb/> in the Chronicle the
                title Morenu Rab means Dr. of the Law; can<lb/> therefore that of Dr. be used with
                all correctness? And, by the way,<lb/> as you have seen <persName>Mr.
                    Myers'</persName> writings, I would, if you do not consid„<lb/>er improper, ask
                your opinion of their merits.</p>
            <p rend="indent(6)">I am, Rev. Sir,</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">Truly yours,</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">
                <persName role="author">David M. Pizal</persName>
            </p>
